    <item>
      <title>Introduction to LaTeX for Scientific Papers</title>
      <link>https://yana-nka.github.io/my-academic-site/en/post/latex-markup/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 30 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://yana-nka.github.io/my-academic-site/en/post/latex-markup/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-latex&#34;&gt;What is LaTeX?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LaTeX is a professional typesetting system widely used in academia. It is the standard for writing scientific papers, dissertations, theses, and journal articles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-latex&#34;&gt;Why LaTeX?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional quality&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; produces beautifully formatted documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automatic numbering&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; of sections, tables, figures, and equations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Convenient bibliography management&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; BibTeX integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support for complex mathematical formulas&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; the best tool for equations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plain text format&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; works with any text editor and version control&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free and cross-platform&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;basic-structure&#34;&gt;Basic Structure&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A minimal LaTeX document:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-latex&#34; data-lang=&#34;latex&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\documentclass&lt;/span&gt;{article}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\title&lt;/span&gt;{My First Article}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\author&lt;/span&gt;{Author Name}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\begin&lt;/span&gt;{document}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\maketitle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\section&lt;/span&gt;{Introduction}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your text here...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;\end&lt;/span&gt;{document}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;formulas&#34;&gt;Formulas&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inline formula: $E = mc^2$
Displayed formula:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$$ \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^2},dx = \sqrt{\pi} $$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;conclusion&#34;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once you master LaTeX, you can professionally format any academic document. It is an essential tool for researchers and students in STEM fields.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
